    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nCurrently if you call `vim.api.nvim__screenshot('~/foo.txt')` neovim immediately crashes.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nnvim --clean\n:lua vim.api.nvim__screenshot('~/foo.txt')\n\nProduces: \n```\nfish: Job 1, 'nvim $argv' terminated by signal SIGSEGV (Address boundary error)\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThis should either display an error message if nvim can't interpret `~` as home, or it should produce a screenshot in the home directory without crashing.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev-519+gbf1d4e9793 Build type: Debug LuaJIT 2.1.1744317938 Run \"nvim -V1 -v\" for more info\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nvim does not have `vim.api.nvim__screenshot()`\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux x86_64 - Kernel 6.14.6-arch1-1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.42.0\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nBuild from source",
